Using CSS, you can use the :hover pseudo class to change the color of the <span> on mouse over.

In your CSS file, you can add the following:

span:hover {
  color: red;
}

This will cause the <span> to change to red when the mouse hovers over it.

To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, you first need to add the footmisc package to your document preamble:

\usepackage{footmisc}

Then, within your document, you can add the footnote to the authors list using the \footnote{} command. For example:

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{footmisc}

\begin{document}

\title{My Article}
\author{John Smith\footnote{Affiliation: XYZ University}, Jane Doe\footnote{Affiliation: ABC Institute}}

\maketitle

\end{document}

This will create a footnote for each author, displaying their affiliation.

#include <stdio.h> 

int fib(int n) 
{ 
  int f[n+2]; // Declare an array to store Fibonacci numbers 
  int i; 

  // Base cases 
  f[0] = 0; 
  f[1] = 1; 

  // Calculate the Fibonacci numbers up to the nth number 
  for (i = 2; i <= n; i++) 
    f[i] = f[i-1] + f[i-2]; 

  return f[n]; 
} 

int main () 
{ 
  int n;

  printf("Enter the nth Fibonacci number: ");
  scanf("%d", &n);
  printf("The %dth Fibonacci number is %d \n", n, fib(n)); 
  return 0; 
}
